    Demo Case 06 - Closed / General Inquiry / Low priority
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the SIXTH of the 10-case demo dataset; together with
    cases 01 through 05 and cases 07 through 10, it satisfies the AAP
    requirement (Section 0.7.4) of "at least 10 demo cases across all
    six statuses and both case types," and contributes to the dataset
    matrix:

        Case 01 - Draft       / General Inquiry / Medium
        Case 02 - Open        / General Inquiry / Medium
        Case 03 - In Progress / General Inquiry / Medium
        Case 04 - Pending     / General Inquiry / Low
        Case 05 - Resolved    / General Inquiry / High
        Case 06 - Closed      / General Inquiry / Low      ## THIS FILE
        Case 07 - Open        / Complaint       / High
        Case 08 - In Progress / Complaint       / Critical
        Case 09 - Resolved    / Complaint       / High
        Case 10 - Closed      / Complaint       / Critical

    The 10-case dataset thus exercises:
      * Every one of the six statuses (Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending,
        Resolved, Closed) - this case occupies the Closed slot for the
        General Inquiry case type
      * Both case types (General Inquiry and Complaint) across the
        full lifecycle - case 06 is the canonical CLOSED GENERAL INQUIRY
        and is the General-Inquiry-flow analog of case 10 (Closed
        Complaint)
      * All four priorities (Low, Medium, High, Critical) - this case
        contributes to the Low bar in the all_cases_by_priority chart
        (alongside case 04 which is Pending / Low); these two cases
        ensure the Low bar has TWO distinct status values represented,
        demonstrating the dashboard correctly aggregates a single
        priority across multiple statuses

    Lifecycle position - WHY Closed / General Inquiry / Low is meaningful:
      A General Inquiry case that has reached Closed status has traversed
      the COMPLETE happy-path lifecycle:
        Draft -> Open -> In Progress -> [optionally Pending] -> Resolved
              -> Closed
      The case is fully terminated; no further updates are permitted by
      the block_terminal_closed business rule. The Low priority is
      appropriate at this lifecycle phase: General Inquiry cases (as
      opposed to Complaints) tend to be lower-urgency informational
      requests that get resolved without crisis-level escalation. By
      assigning Low priority, this case demonstrates that even routine
      low-urgency cases successfully complete the full lifecycle and
      contribute meaningful data to the Manager View dashboards.

