    Authoring rules honored (per AAP Sections 0.7.1 / 0.7.2 and the
    agent prompt's ten authoring rules):

      Rule 1 - Synthetic only (AAP Section 0.7.2 NO-PII clause):
        subject       = "Demo case 06: Closed (General Inquiry)"
        description   = "Synthetic Closed case - completed lifecycle."
                        (no PII; the wording emphasizes the lifecycle
                        position - the case has run to completion and
                        is now terminal; the dash separator avoids any
                        em-dash or special characters that could trip
                        XML parsing)
        requester_name  = "Synthetic Requester Six" (synthetic
                          identifier using the literal word "Synthetic"
                          plus a numeral spelled out for the requester,
                          NOT a real person's name; consistent with the
                          peer convention used by cases 07, 08, 09, 10)
        requester_email = "requester-6@example.invalid"
                          (RFC 2606 / BCP 32 reserved .invalid TLD never
                          resolves to a real domain; the local part uses
                          the NUMERAL "6" matching the file numbering -
                          consistent with the other demo case files'
                          NUMERAL convention for the email local part
