        Unix-style line endings (LF) per AAP file authoring conventions.

      Rule 10 - Date format strictness:
        ServiceNow's GlideDateTime parses string dates in the format
        "YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS" using the instance default time zone (or
        UTC for system-level imports). The two date values below use:
          * 24-hour, zero-padded time (09:00:00 not 9:00:00 AM,
            17:00:00 not 5:00:00 PM)
          * No timezone suffix (no Z, no offset; the import treats the
            value as UTC for the system timezone)
          * Hyphen-separated date (2026-04-10 not 2026/04/10)
          * Single-space date/time separator (not 'T')
        These conventions match the GlideDateTime.setDisplayValue()
        contract documented for ServiceNow scoped applications and
        match the format used by case 10's date overrides.

    Source-side semantic reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported)
    per AAP Section 0.8.1:
      acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java
        ArkCase's CaseFile JPA entity declares ~80 fields including
        cm_case_status (the source for our <status>), cm_case_priority
        (the source for our <priority>), cm_case_type (the source for
        our <type>), cm_case_title (the source for our <subject>),
        cm_case_details (Lob; the source for our <description>), and
        cm_case_closed (Temporal TIMESTAMP; the source for our
        <closed_date>). The ServiceNow target collapses ArkCase's ~80
        fields to the user-prompt's 12-field schema (number, type,
        status, priority, subject, description, opened_date,
        closed_date, assigned_group, assigned_agent, requester_name,
        requester_email - plus the optional pending_reason). ArkCase's
        Disposition.java entity captures closeDate and dispositionType
        for case closure metadata; the ServiceNow target uses only
        closed_date (no separate disposition entity per the POC's
        minimal-scope rule). ArkCase's queue-handler-driven default
        status flow ("DRAFT" -> "ACTIVE" via CaseFileQueueHandler.java)
        is replaced in this POC by Flow Designer's
        general_inquiry_state_machine.xml; ArkCase's
        ChangeCaseFileStateService.java is replaced by the
        x_casemgmt_CaseTransitionValidator script include.

