      - Scope-identifier validation: the concrete scope identifier `casemgmt` is used verbatim in the sys_class_name, sys_update_name,
        all reference values, and the file path; ServiceNow Update Set imports use a standard XML parser, so the scope id is concrete in the XML before export. The same identifier is used consistently across every cross-reference in this file.

    Key insights (per the agent prompt):
      1. Demo case 06 is the canonical Closed General Inquiry case; the
         General-Inquiry-flow analog of demo case 10 (Closed Complaint).
      2. THIS CASE IS ONE OF EXACTLY TWO INPUTS TO THE avg_time_to_close
         WIDGET. Without case 06, the widget would have only one sample
         (case 10) and degenerate to a constant. With both cases, the
         widget shows a meaningful average of approximately 16 days.
      3. THIS CASE IS THE CANONICAL block_terminal_closed TEST FOR THE
         GENERAL INQUIRY FLOW. When the operator attempts ANY update
         on this case, the verbatim error "Closed cases are terminal
         and cannot be modified." appears (per AAP Section 0.5.5).
      4. The status "Closed" has a capital C. Not lowercase, not all
         caps. The exact choice value is "Closed" per AAP Section 0.5.7.
      5. Both date fields MUST be explicit XML values. Unlike cases
         01-05 (which let business rules auto-set dates), this case's
         dates are explicit because:
           * Insert with status = Closed does NOT trigger the Resolved
             -> Closed update path that sets closed_date.
           * The auto-set opened_date would equal "now", giving a zero
             gap to closed_date that breaks the avg_time_to_close
             widget.
      6. The dates use UTC and 24-hour format per ServiceNow's
         GlideDateTime convention.
      7. No tasks, no parties on this case. Closed cases are fully
         concluded; no children are seeded in the demo dataset.
      8. The case appears in the Closed slice/bar of dashboards but NOT
         in the Agent Workspace's "My Open Cases" list (filter excludes
         Closed and Resolved).
      9. The cases_opened_30d widget includes this case. With
         opened_date approximately 20 days ago (within the 30-day
         window), the case is included in the count.
     10. The dates are computed at file-generation time based on
         "today" (2026-04-30 UTC). They are NOT placeholders or
         template values; they are concrete static datetime literals
         valid at the time of generation. The Update Set XML is a
         static document; the values do not re-evaluate at import time.
     11. The Low priority on this case complements case 04 (Pending /
         Low) to ensure the all_cases_by_priority bar chart's Low bar
         contains TWO distinct status values, demonstrating the
         dashboard correctly aggregates a single priority across
         multiple statuses (rather than degenerating to a single-
         status aggregation).
     12. The General Inquiry type on this case complements case 10
         (Complaint) to ensure the avg_time_to_close widget computes
         across BOTH case types, demonstrating the widget filters on
         status=Closed without further filtering on type.
